🌿 My concluding reflection
Dear Friends, I believe Sarga 179 opens with one of the boldest declarations in all of Advaita: it does not begin by proving Brahman through the world; it begins with Brahman and asks us to reinterpret the world in its light. That is why the first five verses are so foundational. Everything that follows—Māyā, causation, multiplicity, and the unity of seer and seen—rests upon this one insight:
Consciousness is not a property of the body.
The body is an appearance within Consciousness.
This is the doorway through which Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha now invites every earnest seeker to enter. 🌿🕉️
